[{"text": "So the type of magic I like,\nand I'm a magician,", "start": 15.64, "duration": 2.877}, {"text": "is magic that uses technology\nto create illusions.", "start": 18.541, "duration": 3.174}, {"text": "So I would like to show you\nsomething I've been working on.", "start": 22.26, "duration": 2.81}, {"text": "It's an application", "start": 25.094, "duration": 1.247}, {"text": "that I think will be useful for artists --\nmultimedia artists in particular.", "start": 26.365, "duration": 4.643}, {"text": "It synchronizes videos\nacross multiple screens of mobile devices.", "start": 31.032, "duration": 3.993}, {"text": "I borrowed these three iPods\nfrom people here in the audience", "start": 35.421, "duration": 2.921}, {"text": "to show you what I mean.", "start": 38.366, "duration": 1.206}, {"text": "And I'm going to use them to tell you\na little bit about my favorite subject:", "start": 43.036, "duration": 4.668}, {"text": "deception.", "start": 47.728, "duration": 1.064}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 51.991, "duration": 2.021}, {"text": "One of my favorite magicians\nis Karl Germain.", "start": 54.036, "duration": 4.719}, {"text": "He had this wonderful trick\nwhere a rosebush would bloom", "start": 58.779, "duration": 4.463}, {"text": "right in front of your eyes.", "start": 63.266, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "But it was his production of a butterfly\nthat was the most beautiful.", "start": 65.702, "duration": 5.251}, {"text": "(Recording) Announcer:\nLadies and gentlemen,", "start": 70.977, "duration": 2.857}, {"text": "the creation of life.", "start": 73.858, "duration": 2.378}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 76.26, "duration": 1.976}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 78.26, "duration": 3.691}, {"text": "Marco Tempest: When asked about deception,", "start": 81.975, "duration": 2.218}, {"text": "he said this:", "start": 84.217, "duration": 1.104}, {"text": "Announcer: Magic\nis the only honest profession.", "start": 87.22, "duration": 2.949}, {"text": "A magician promises to deceive you --", "start": 90.711, "duration": 2.633}, {"text": "and he does.", "start": 93.368, "duration": 1.386}, {"text": "MT: I like to think of myself\nas an honest magician.", "start": 94.778, "duration": 3.473}, {"text": "I use a lot of tricks,", "start": 98.275, "duration": 1.687}, {"text": "which means that sometimes\nI have to lie to you.", "start": 99.986, "duration": 3.944}, {"text": "Now I feel bad about that.", "start": 104.836, "duration": 2.618}, {"text": "But people lie every day.", "start": 107.899, "duration": 2.477}, {"text": "(Ringing)", "start": 110.4, "duration": 1.024}, {"text": "Hold on.", "start": 111.448, "duration": 1.013}, {"text": "Phone: Hey, where are you?", "start": 112.485, "duration": 1.655}, {"text": "MT: Stuck in traffic. I'll be there soon.", "start": 114.164, "duration": 2.362}, {"text": "You've all done it.", "start": 117.257, "duration": 1.071}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 118.748, "duration": 1.492}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 120.264, "duration": 1.024}, {"text": "Right: I'll be ready\nin just a minute, darling.", "start": 121.312, "duration": 2.349}, {"text": "Center: It's just what I've always wanted.", "start": 123.685, "duration": 2.778}, {"text": "Left: You were great.", "start": 126.906, "duration": 1.33}, {"text": "MT: Deception,", "start": 128.993, "duration": 1.754}, {"text": "it's a fundamental part of life.", "start": 130.771, "duration": 2.981}, {"text": "Now polls show", "start": 134.508, "duration": 1.405}, {"text": "that men tell twice\nas many lies as women --", "start": 135.937, "duration": 4.299}, {"text": "assuming the women\nthey asked told the truth.", "start": 140.26, "duration": 2.896}, {"text": "(Laughing)", "start": 143.18, "duration": 1.135}, {"text": "We deceive to gain advantage", "start": 144.339, "duration": 2.897}, {"text": "and to hide our weaknesses.", "start": 147.26, "duration": 3.386}, {"text": "The Chinese general Sun Tzu said\nthat all war was based on deception.", "start": 150.67, "duration": 5.566}, {"text": "Oscar Wilde said\nthe same thing of romance.", "start": 157.106, "duration": 4.13}, {"text": "Some people deceive", "start": 161.26, "duration": 2.713}, {"text": "for money.", "start": 163.997, "duration": 1.215}, {"text": "Let's play a game.", "start": 165.544, "duration": 1.663}, {"text": "Three cards, three chances.", "start": 168.552, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "Announcer: One five will get you 10,\n10 will get you 20.", "start": 171.87, "duration": 2.674}, {"text": "Now, where's the lady?", "start": 174.568, "duration": 1.852}, {"text": "Where is the queen?", "start": 176.444, "duration": 1.52}, {"text": "MT: This one?", "start": 179.158, "duration": 1.078}, {"text": "Sorry. You lose.", "start": 180.748, "duration": 2.089}, {"text": "Well, I didn't deceive you.", "start": 182.861, "duration": 2.529}, {"text": "You deceived yourself.", "start": 185.414, "duration": 2.617}, {"text": "Self-deception.", "start": 188.612, "duration": 1.262}, {"text": "That's when we convince ourselves\nthat a lie is the truth.", "start": 190.565, "duration": 3.892}, {"text": "Sometimes it's hard to tell the two apart.", "start": 194.863, "duration": 2.397}, {"text": "Compulsive gamblers\nare experts at self-deception.", "start": 200.165, "duration": 3.566}, {"text": "(Slot machine)", "start": 203.755, "duration": 1.619}, {"text": "They believe they can win.", "start": 205.398, "duration": 1.952}, {"text": "They forget the times they lose.", "start": 207.89, "duration": 2.683}, {"text": "The brain is very good at forgetting.", "start": 210.597, "duration": 2.789}, {"text": "Bad experiences are quickly forgotten.", "start": 213.87, "duration": 2.619}, {"text": "Bad experiences quickly disappear.", "start": 217.076, "duration": 3.443}, {"text": "Which is why in this vast\nand lonely cosmos,", "start": 221.265, "duration": 2.917}, {"text": "we are so wonderfully optimistic.", "start": 224.206, "duration": 3.198}, {"text": "Our self-deception\nbecomes a positive illusion --", "start": 228.19, "duration": 4.107}, {"text": "why movies are able to take us\nonto extraordinary adventures;", "start": 232.321, "duration": 4.729}, {"text": "why we believe Romeo\nwhen he says he loves Juliet;", "start": 237.074, "duration": 3.778}, {"text": "and why single notes of music,", "start": 240.876, "duration": 2.708}, {"text": "when played together,", "start": 243.608, "duration": 2.318}, {"text": "become a sonata and conjure up meaning.", "start": 245.95, "duration": 2.657}, {"text": "That's \"Clair De lune.\"", "start": 249.37, "duration": 1.418}, {"text": "Its composer, called Debussy,", "start": 250.812, "duration": 2.617}, {"text": "said that art was\nthe greatest deception of all.", "start": 253.453, "duration": 3.796}, {"text": "Art is a deception\nthat creates real emotions --", "start": 258.36, "duration": 5.224}, {"text": "a lie that creates a truth.", "start": 263.608, "duration": 3.232}, {"text": "And when you give yourself\nover to that deception,", "start": 267.227, "duration": 4.181}, {"text": "it becomes magic.", "start": 271.432, "duration": 2.024}, {"text": "[MAGIC]", "start": 274.733, "duration": 1.429}, {"text": "(Music fades slowly)", "start": 278.856, "duration": 1.817}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 281.538, "duration": 2.485}, {"text": "Thank you. Thank you very much.", "start": 294.228, "duration": 2.952}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 297.204, "duration": 2.702}]